header.gameNote: CABLE CAR CLASSIC AT SANTA CLARA CA

article.headline: SMU 67, Alcorn St. 52
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- Jalen Jones had 19 points and nine rebounds to lead SMU to a 67-52 victory against Alcorn State on Saturday night in the third-place game of the Cable Car Classic. Nick Russell added 14 points and Shawn Williams 12 for the Mustangs (9-4). Marquiz Baker scored 24 points for the Braves (2-11), but he shot just 7 of 20 from the floor, including 4 of 15 from 3-point range. SMU -- which shot 52.4 percent (22 of 42) from the floor, outrebounded Alcorn State 35-23 and enjoyed a 34-16 scoring edge in the paint -- led 33-23 at halftime and built the cushion to 18 points in the second half. The Mustangs made 20 of 21 (95.2 percent) free-throw attempts, the sixth-best percentage in school history. The Braves shot just 32.7 percent (16 of 49) from the field.
